    "created_at": "2016-06-20T11:43:21Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-06-20T11:45:29Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There are still two major aspects missing compared to original TS:\n- Burning trees would continously take damage as long as the fire animation was running. So I actually doubt using `WithDamageOverlay` is the right approach, it doesn't loop long enough either. You might be better off using `Burns`, though in its current state that trait is too limited, it will need to be made upgradable, activatable via `DamageType` and the animation part split off to a render trait and unhardcoded at least.\n- Trees would incinerate nearby trees when the flames grew larger. This can be done by using `ExplosionOnDamageTransition` to fire a weapon at `Critical` (or maybe at `Heavy`) that does nothing but incinerate (needs a large enough spread of course, but make sure it doesn't exceed the 8 adjacent cells around the tree).\n"
  },
